mergers.merger_description:
The Acquisition is a private equity financial investment concerning the acquisition of DSM-Firmenich AG’s Animal Nutrition & Health business (the **Target**) by the following newly formed companies:

1. Specialty Bidco B.V.;
2. Specialty (U.S.) Bidco, Inc.;
3. Essential Bidco B.V.; and
4. Essential (U.S.) Bidco, Inc.

These companies are all indirectly controlled by funds advised or managed by affiliates of CVC Capital Partners plc (**CVC Capital Partners**), a public limited company incorporated in Jersey and listed in Amsterdam.

The CVC Network is a global alternative investment manager focused on private equity, credit, infrastructure and secondaries, and includes CVC Capital Partners, each of its subsidiaries, and the CVC Funds.

The seller is DSM B.V., a private limited liability company incorporated in the Netherlands and part of DSM-Firmenich AG. The Target is a global provider of science-based animal nutrition and health solutions for livestock producers and feed manufacturers. Its global activities span:

1. vitamins and carotenoids;
2. premixes;
3. performance solutions;
4. aroma ingredients; and
5. precision services.

MedHealth Pty Ltd (**MedHealth**) proposes to acquire all of the assets of the business of Connect Allied Health (**Connect**) pursuant to a business sale and purchase agreement (the **Acquisition**).

Founded in 2016, Connect is a multi-disciplinary allied health services provider operating in South Australia. Connect provides clinic and community-based speech therapy, occupational therapy, physiotherapy, positive behavioural support, psychology and podiatry services across Adelaide and the Riverland.

MedHealth is an Australian subsidiary of the ExamWorks Group (**ExamWorks**). ExamWorks is a United States-based independent provider of services including independent medical examinations, peer reviews, bill reviews, Medicare compliance, record retrieval, document management and related services.

ExamWorks operates in Australia through MedHealth, which provides a range of services to a variety of businesses and consumers across the private and public sectors.

MedHealth’s Allied Health Services Division provides services to a wide range of patients who include NDIS participants, private health insurance clients and customers from other funding sources (for example, Department of Veterans’ Affairs, Medicare, My Aged Care and workers compensation) across Australia through a number of brands including:

* Ability Action Australia (Nationwide including SA);
* Outcomes Connect (VIC, QLD, NSW);
* AIM Therapy (WA);
* Hanrahan Health (NSW);
* Living to the Max (SA);
* Real Therapy Solutions (NSW);
* Pepper Kids Therapy (QLD); and
* Enunciate Allied Health (NSW).

Regent Motors Pty Ltd (**Regent Motors Group**) proposes to acquire a portfolio of franchised automotive dealerships and associated real property located in Mandurah, Western Australia, currently operated by WA Automotive Pty Ltd, controlled by the Lane Group (the **Vendor**) (the **Acquisition**).

Regent Motors Group is a wholly Australian-owned automotive retail group headquartered in Perth, Western Australia. Regent Motors Group owns and operates franchised motor vehicle dealerships across Western Australia and the Northern Territory, supplying new and used motor vehicles across a range of OEM brands including Ford, Toyota, Hyundai, Suzuki, BMW, Mini, MG, Geely, GMSV, Isuzu Ute, Subaru, and Volkswagen. Regent Motors Group also provides vehicle servicing and repairs, genuine parts and accessories, fleet sales and service, and facilitates finance, insurance, and aftercare products in connection with vehicle transactions.

The target businesses comprise six franchised retail dealerships and associated storage facilities at the following Mandurah locations:

* 113 Pinjarra Road (Ford);
* 115 Pinjarra Road (Mitsubishi);
* 117 Pinjarra Road (Hyundai);
* 8 Randall Street (Kia);
* 53 Pinjarra Road (Nissan);
* 55 Pinjarra Road (Suzuki); and
* storage premises at 24, 26 and 23 Boundary Road.

The target businesses supply new and used motor vehicles for those brands, together with vehicle servicing and repairs, parts and accessories, fleet services, and finance and insurance facilitation.

The Acquisition will be effected through the purchase of the relevant business assets, franchise agreements, and real property associated with each site.
